  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Tensile reduction of area (RA) values from Table I: AL 22.2%, AT 26.8%, BL 22.7%, BT 27.2%, CL 24.2%, CT 19.4%.",
    "A fatigue S-N data table listed below Figure 1 gives cycles 10^5 at 420 MPa, 10^6 at 320 MPa, and 10^7 at 230 MPa; the text did not explicitly attribute these data points to specimen BL or BT specifically.",
    "In alloy B, fatigue cracks initiated at slip bands and propagated along a direction roughly normal to the applied stress.",
    "For the same alloy type, longitudinal specimens possessed higher tensile strength and lower elongation than transverse specimens, though the differences were not significant.",
    "Previous literature reported Fe-Mn-Al-C alloys possess yield and tensile strengths about 50% higher than conventional 300 series stainless steels with equivalent ductility, and tensile strength can reach 1033 MPa at 40% elongation with proper ageing."
